HEADWORD: Hexeikosane
<hw>Hex*ei"ko*sane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hex-</ets> + <ets>eikosane</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(chem.)</fld>
<def>A hydrocarbon, <chform>C26H54</chform>, resembling paraffine; -- so
called because each molecule has <xex>twenty-six</xex> atoms of
carbon.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>hexacosane</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hexene</ent>⟦br⟧
